### =============================================
### SkyWay API Testing (REST Client for VS Code)
### Install "REST Client" extension, then click
### "Send Request" above any request block.
### =============================================

### ---------- HEALTH CHECK ----------

GET http://localhost:5000/api/health

### ---------- FLIGHTS ----------

### Search Flights (Mumbai → Goa)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/flights?from=Mumbai&to=Goa&date=2026-04-25

###

### Search Flights (Delhi → Dubai)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/flights?from=Delhi&to=Dubai&date=2026-05-01

###

### Get Popular Routes
GET http://localhost:5000/api/flights/popular

###

### Multi-City Search
POST http://localhost:5000/api/flights/multi
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "legs": [
    { "from": "Mumbai", "to": "Delhi", "date": "2026-05-01" },
    { "from": "Delhi", "to": "Bangalore", "date": "2026-05-03" }
  ]
}

### ---------- HOTELS ----------

### Search Hotels (All Cities)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/hotels?city=&checkin=2026-04-25&checkout=2026-04-27&guests=2

###

### Search Hotels (Jaipur)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/hotels?city=Jaipur&checkin=2026-04-25&checkout=2026-04-27&guests=2

###

### Search Hotels (Singapore)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/hotels?city=Singapore&checkin=2026-05-01&checkout=2026-05-04&guests=2

###

### Search Hotels (Manali)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/hotels?city=Manali&checkin=2026-05-10&checkout=2026-05-12&guests=3

###

### Get Available Cities
GET http://localhost:5000/api/hotels/cities

###

### Book a Hotel
POST http://localhost:5000/api/hotels/book
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "hotel": {
    "name": "Pink City Palace",
    "city": "Jaipur",
    "stars": 5,
    "price": 11499,
    "image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1587474260584-136574528ed5?w=400&q=80"
  },
  "checkin": "2026-04-25",
  "checkout": "2026-04-27",
  "guests": 2,
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com"
}

###

### Get Hotel Bookings
GET http://localhost:5000/api/hotels/bookings

### ---------- DEALS ----------

### Get All Deals
GET http://localhost:5000/api/deals

###

### Get Domestic Deals
GET http://localhost:5000/api/deals?category=Domestic

###

### Get International Deals
GET http://localhost:5000/api/deals?category=International

###

### Get Weekend Deals
GET http://localhost:5000/api/deals?category=Weekend

### ---------- AUTH ----------

### Register New User (Note: Aadhaar PDF upload requires Postman/Thunder Client)
### This will fail without multipart form - use Thunder Client for file upload
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Rahul",
  "lastName": "Sharma",
  "email": "rahul@example.com",
  "phone": "9876543210",
  "password": "pass123",
  "address": "123 MG Road",
  "city": "Mumbai",
  "state": "Maharashtra",
  "pincode": "400001"
}

###

### Login
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "rahul@example.com",
  "password": "pass123"
}

###

### Login (Wrong Password - should fail)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "rahul@example.com",
  "password": "wrongpass"
}

###

### Forgot Password
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "rahul@example.com"
}

###

### Forgot Email (by phone)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/forgot-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "9876543210"
}

### ---------- BOOKINGS ----------

### Create Flight Booking
POST http://localhost:5000/api/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "flight": {
    "airline": "IndiGo",
    "code": "6E",
    "from": "Mumbai",
    "to": "Goa",
    "price": 2499,
    "dep": "06:00",
    "arr": "07:10",
    "duration": "1h 10m",
    "stops": "Direct"
  },
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "phone": "9876543210"
}

### ---------- PAYMENTS ----------

### Simulate Payment
POST http://localhost:5000/api/payments/create-order
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 5000
}
